{
  "texts": [
    "Further, Narin et al. proposed an automated CNN based diagnostic model for detecting pneumonia caused by coronavirus (Narin et al. 2021).",
    "They developed pre-trained AI models using the X-ray radiographs of healthy individuals, patients with COVID-19, patients with viral pneumonia, and patients with bacterial pneumonia.",
    "The reported accuracy in classification reached up to 96%.",
    "In addition to COVID-19, ML models have been built to assist in the diagnosis of other infectious diseases such as urinary tract infections (UTIs), which are often associated with diagnostic errors.",
    "Taylor et al."
  ]
}